TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bruno, Valentina
AU  - Shin, Hyun Song
T1  - Global Dollar Credit and Carry Trades: A Firm-Level Analysis
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhw099
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 3
SP  - 703
EP  - 749
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We conduct a firm-level analysis of borrowing in US dollars by nonfinancial corporates from outside the United States. We find that emerging market firms with already high cash holdings are more likely to issue US dollar-denominated bonds, especially during periods when the dollar carry trade is more favorable. The proceeds of the dollar bond issuance add to the firm’s cash holdings more than other sources of funds. The evidence points to financial decisions that resemble carry trades, rather than to precautionary borrowing in anticipation of future financing needs.Received November 30, 2015; editorial decision July 20, 2016 by Editor Itay Goldstein
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhw099
ER  - 



