TY  - JOUR
AU  - Berg, Tobias
AU  - Saunders, Anthony
AU  - Steffen, Sascha
AU  - Streitz, Daniel
T1  - Mind the Gap: The Difference between U.S. and European Loan Rates
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhw097
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 3
SP  - 948
EP  - 987
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We analyze pricing differences between U.S. and European syndicated loans over the 1992–2014 period. We explicitly distinguish credit lines from term loans. For credit lines, U.S. borrowers pay significantly higher spreads, but lower fees, resulting in similar total costs of borrowing in both markets. Credit line usage is more cyclical in the United States, which provides a rationale for the pricing structure difference. For term loans, we analyze the channels of the cross-country loan price differential and document the importance of: the composition of term loan borrowers and the loan supply by institutional investors and foreign banks.Received September 18, 2015; editorial decision July 13, 2016 by Editor Philip Strahan.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhw097
ER  - 



